text: Cacheu is a region in western Guinea-Bissau, on the border with Senegal. The regional capital is Cacheu. As of the 2009 census, 192,508 people lived there. It has an area of . == Sectors == * Bigene * Bula * Cacheu (capital) * Caió * Canghungo * São Domingos Category:Regions of Guinea-Bissau
